question6_key3: Prime numbers woh numbers hote hai jo sirf 1 aur apne aap se divisible hote hain. Jaise
question6_key4: `13` prime hai kyunki `13` sirf `13` aur `1` se perfectly divide hota hai. Aur kisi bhi number se perfectly divide nahi hota.
question6_key5: `4` prime nahi hai kyunki `4` apne aap se aur `2` aur `1` se perfectly divide hota hai.
question6_key6: Prime number ke liye aapko check karna hoga ki woh number kaun kaun se numbers se divisible hai. Yeh `loop` chala ke kar sakte ho.
